    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Holyhead.</placeName>
                    <date>July 20<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. 1842.</date>
                    <salute>Sir,</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">

<p>I have again examined my Section and also the Field Book from which it was laid down, but on neither is the Village of Bethesda shewn. The nearest point I can give you to that place is Tyn-y-maes (a small Inn where the Mail changes horses) which is 604.9 <hi rend="superscript">Feet</hi> above the Road in front of the Hotel at Holyhead.</p>
<p>I remain | Sir | Your obed<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> Servant | John Provis <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/> Chas. Darwin Esq<hi rend="superscript">re</hi></p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
        
    
        
